6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"dYdX's 1-hour funding intervals create more frequent arbitrage opportunities but require faster position management compared to Phemex's standard 8-hour cycles. The decentralized nature of dYdX means funding rates are determined purely by on-chain order flow, while Phemex uses traditional mark price methodology. dYdX's lower liquidity post-migration can lead to more volatile funding rates, whereas Phemex maintains steadier rates through market maker programs. Both exchanges use the standard funding rate formula but dYdX's frequent settlements can compound costs or profits more rapidly."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lb",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange has better funding rate opportunities?","answer":"dYdX's 1-hour funding intervals create 8x more opportunities per day than Phemex, but require more active management. Phemex's lower maker fees (0.01% vs 0.02%) can offset the reduced frequency for larger positions."},{"question":"How do trading fees compare for arbitrage strategies?","answer":"Phemex has lower maker fees (0.01%) favoring limit orders, while dYdX charges 0.02% but offers decentralized execution. Taker fees are similar at 0.05-0.06%, making order type selection crucial for profitability."},{"question":"Which platform is more reliable for funding arbitrage?","answer":"Phemex offers more consistent liquidity and established infrastructure, while dYdX provides censorship resistance but with post-migration volume challenges. Both have proven track records but serve different risk appetites."},{"question":"What are the settlement differences for arbitrage?","answer":"dYdX settles in USDC on-chain requiring gas fees, while Phemex uses off-chain USDT settlement. This affects cross-exchange arbitrage strategies and withdrawal timing between the platforms."}]}]
